WEBVTT

00:02.722 --> 00:32.146
I dreamed I went to heaven And you were there with me We walked along the streets of gold Beside the crystal sea

00:33.506 --> 01:03.154
We heard the angels singing Then someone called your name You turned and saw this young man And he was smiling as he came He said, friend, you may not know me now And then he said, but wait You used to teach my Sunday school

01:05.986 --> 01:12.353
Every week you would say a prayer before the class would start.

01:13.494 --> 01:21.022
And one day when you said that prayer, I asked Jesus in my heart.

01:22.764 --> 01:29.391
Thank you for giving to the Lord.

01:31.674 --> 01:35.378
I am a life that was changed.

01:42.594 --> 02:11.698
I am so glad you gave Then another man stood before you And said, remember the time A missionary came to your church And his pictures made you cry You didn't have much money

02:11.970 --> 02:14.393
But you gave it anyway.

02:16.536 --> 02:24.926
Jesus took the gift you gave and that's why I'm here today.

02:25.066 --> 02:34.598
So thank you for giving to the Lord.

02:34.618 --> 02:38.002
I am a life that was changed.

02:50.146 --> 03:18.130
So glad you gave One by one they came Far as the eye could see Each life somehow touched By your generosity Little things that you had done Sacrifice is made

03:19.554 --> 03:46.610
unnoticed on the earth but in heaven now proclaim and I know up in heaven you're not supposed to cry but I am almost sure there were tears in your eyes as Jesus took your hand

03:46.978 --> 03:50.602
And you stood before the Lord.

03:50.622 --> 03:54.527
He said, my child, look around you.

03:55.408 --> 04:00.614
Great is your reward.

04:02.996 --> 04:11.286
Thank you for giving to the Lord.

04:11.306 --> 04:14.930
I am a life that was changed.

04:27.586 --> 04:31.432
So glad you gave.

04:32.634 --> 04:40.786
Oh, thank you for giving to the Lord.

04:43.049 --> 04:46.194
I am a life that was changed.

05:11.650 --> 05:36.477
Let's open in prayer.

05:38.659 --> 05:41.042
Heavenly Father, we're so grateful to know

05:43.106 --> 05:46.950
that everything we do for you counts, it matters.

05:47.851 --> 05:59.262
We're so thankful that you take our service, our efforts, everything done in your name and in your will, and you use them to work in the lives of those around us.

06:00.843 --> 06:09.351
May we always have a spirit of service, Lord, to bring your love, your truth, and your saving grace to those in our world.

06:10.953 --> 06:12.274
Visit with us now, Father.

06:12.962 --> 06:15.024
Bless this time as we study your word.

06:16.026 --> 06:20.150
Give us open ears and open hearts to hear the message you have for us today.

06:21.211 --> 06:23.154
In the precious name of Jesus, we pray.

06:24.095 --> 06:24.395
Amen.

06:26.658 --> 06:34.206
Mordecai Ham was an American tent revival preacher in the late 1800s and early 1900s.

06:34.326 --> 06:40.914
And in 1934, he was preaching a tent revival in Charlotte, North Carolina.

06:42.210 --> 06:46.476
Two 14 year old boys saw the tent and the commotion of people.

06:47.397 --> 06:53.745
And they heard this bold preaching about the unwavering unrelenting love of a father.

06:55.167 --> 07:03.879
Well, their curiosity led them to the tent, but as they walked up, they realized there was no room, no seats available, it was packed.

07:05.180 --> 07:09.586
And as they walked away, heads hung low and usher.

07:10.434 --> 07:20.108
whose name no one knows to this day, ran up to these two 14-year-old boys and said, boys, we can find two seats together for you to sit and listen.

07:21.850 --> 07:22.872
He walked them back.

07:23.132 --> 07:28.259
He asked a couple of people to scoot over, and he found those two boys' seats.

07:29.601 --> 07:38.514
Well, that day, they ended up giving their lives to Christ and consecrating themselves to God's purpose in their generation.

07:39.874 --> 07:50.447
One of those boys was Billy Graham, who ended up preaching the gospel to more people than anyone else has ever preached to in the history of the world.

07:51.789 --> 07:53.551
The other's name was Grady Wilson.

07:55.133 --> 08:01.181
Grady Wilson was the man who ended up organizing all of Billy Graham's evangelistic crusades.

08:03.604 --> 08:04.686
He changed the world.

08:07.309 --> 08:08.210
Not Billy Graham.

08:09.346 --> 08:12.851
not Grady Wilson, not Mordecai Ham, the usher.

08:14.594 --> 08:21.324
The usher, the one man who saw two 14-year-old boys walking away from the faith and said, not on my watch.

08:22.706 --> 08:23.187
Not today.

08:23.487 --> 08:24.389
Get back here, boys.

08:25.751 --> 08:28.215
See, your job isn't to change the world.

08:29.496 --> 08:33.643
It's to change somebody's world.

08:33.663 --> 08:34.564
We have a job to do.

08:36.527 --> 08:38.450
Our job is to run into the breach

08:38.946 --> 08:48.818
You see, there's been a spiritual breach and our job is to run into the breach and say, not today, not on our watch, not while we're here.

08:51.061 --> 09:05.138
Because the smallest act done for Christ, the smallest act to point people to Christ, the smallest act to show Christ and His love to those who are searching can change somebody's life forever.

09:07.426 --> 09:12.052
small acts of service with eternal implications.

09:14.034 --> 09:20.142
Scripture is filled with acts of sacrifice that changed somebody's world.

09:22.105 --> 09:26.090
And I was reminded of one scripture story recently.

09:28.092 --> 09:35.602
A few months ago, Ed and the maintenance crew made up of Cameron and Mike Pooson, Mike Buys, and Keith

09:36.034 --> 09:37.596
were up on the roof of this building.

09:38.817 --> 09:48.910
And they were cleaning up all the tree needles and the leaves and the fallen branches that would clog the water drains before the rainy season came.

09:49.811 --> 09:52.494
It's a critical ministry to keep things from flooding.

09:54.076 --> 09:58.882
And I was thinking how ministry comes in so many different shapes and sizes and flavors.

10:00.124 --> 10:03.688
I remember when the roof was put on and the crew was adding tar to it.

10:03.708 --> 10:05.330
It was a ministry of building.

10:07.298 --> 10:14.347
And I remember when repairs were made to fix leaks around the HVAC units, it was a ministry of repairing.

10:15.488 --> 10:20.254
And in this day in the fall, it was a ministry of cleaning and clearing.

10:21.716 --> 10:28.745
Now, I didn't really think about roof destruction as a viable ministry, but it's happened.

10:29.846 --> 10:36.434
In fact, a hole in the roof is exactly what was needed one day when four men

10:37.250 --> 10:38.492
said, not on our watch.

10:40.434 --> 10:43.858
And they helped save the life and the soul of a helpless man.

10:45.440 --> 10:46.942
Let's look at our text this morning.

10:47.002 --> 10:50.327
Turn with me to Mark chapter 2.

10:50.367 --> 11:00.319
We're going to read about four men, four men whose resourceful, sacrificial, immediate, and reckless act of love changed somebody's world forever.

11:02.202 --> 11:05.586
Mark chapter 2, for some context, we're told earlier in Mark

11:06.306 --> 11:10.010
that Jesus had made his ministry headquarters in Capernaum.

11:11.132 --> 11:19.662
And he had been away teaching and performing miracles, and now he'd come back home back to his home base.

11:19.842 --> 11:21.063
And he's preaching in a house.

11:21.123 --> 11:22.885
We don't know whose house, but it's packed.

11:24.768 --> 11:26.830
And we're going to read from verse one to verse 12.

11:27.090 --> 11:27.511
Let's go.

11:28.512 --> 11:33.618
A few days later, when Jesus again entered Capernaum, the people heard that he had come home.

11:34.434 --> 11:39.580
They gathered in such large numbers that there was no room left, not even outside the door.

11:40.621 --> 11:42.063
And he preached the word to them.

11:43.444 --> 11:47.189
Some men came bringing to him a paralyzed man carried by four of them.

11:48.210 --> 11:59.163
Since they could not get him to Jesus because of the crowd, they made an opening in the roof above Jesus by digging through it and then lowered the mat the man was lying on.

12:00.384 --> 12:02.066
When Jesus saw their faith,

12:02.562 --> 12:06.526
He said to the paralyzed man, son, your sins are forgiven.

12:08.788 --> 12:09.248
Here we go.

12:09.308 --> 12:15.454
Now some teachers of the law were sitting there thinking to themselves, why does this fellow talk like that?

12:15.575 --> 12:16.475
He's blaspheming.

12:17.136 --> 12:18.938
Who can forgive sins but God alone?

12:20.279 --> 12:24.623
Immediately Jesus knew in his spirit that this was what they were thinking in their hearts.

12:25.664 --> 12:27.506
And he said to them, why are you thinking these things?

12:28.367 --> 12:31.730
Which is easier to say to this paralyzed man, your sins are forgiven

12:31.810 --> 12:34.052
or to say, get up, take your mat and walk.

12:36.555 --> 12:41.019
But I want you to know that the Son of man has authority on earth to forgive sins.

12:42.080 --> 12:45.683
So he said to the man, I tell you, get up, take your mat and go home.

12:46.664 --> 12:51.489
He got up, took his mat and walked out in full view of them all.

12:52.510 --> 12:57.615
This amazed everyone, and they praised God, saying, we have never seen anything like this.

12:59.477 --> 13:00.818
You can picture it, can't you?

13:01.218 --> 13:06.904
No sooner had Jesus come into this house, then once again, a huge multitude follows.

13:07.625 --> 13:12.711
And they're pressed together in order to hear him teach and watch him perform his powerful works.

13:13.572 --> 13:15.193
And we can just see the scene.

13:16.074 --> 13:20.379
So many people were pressing about that the whole house was filled to the brim.

13:20.639 --> 13:22.501
And not only that, but they were standing outside.

13:22.521 --> 13:24.143
You couldn't even see the door anymore.

13:27.607 --> 13:30.290
For some background in Palestine at the time,

13:31.842 --> 13:37.430
The normal structure of a house was one story with walls and a flat roof on top.

13:38.432 --> 13:41.717
And roofs were normally constructed with beams across the walls.

13:42.898 --> 13:46.183
And then between the beams were interlaced sticks and reeds.

13:47.004 --> 13:51.331
And within the reeds and sticks was woven kind of a thatch like we know of thatched roofs.

13:52.833 --> 14:00.084
There were stairs that went outside the building up to the roof because the roof was the place people would congregate.

14:00.104 --> 14:01.746
They would go there for fresh air.

14:01.986 --> 14:06.932
They would often eat their meals there or receive visitors on the roof.

14:07.213 --> 14:09.476
It was kind of like how we have decks today.

14:11.759 --> 14:16.665
Now, we don't know much about this paralyzed man, but we know he was desperate.

14:18.107 --> 14:23.754
Desperate for healing, desperate for feeling, desperate to walk, to move his arms and legs.

14:24.735 --> 14:27.779
No doctor could help him, else they would have.

14:27.799 --> 14:29.842
He had exhausted earthly solutions.

14:30.274 --> 14:36.541
But clearly he had heard about this man, Jesus, and his amazing miracles.

14:37.382 --> 14:42.507
The one who made the blind see again who healed lepers, who cast out demons.

14:42.827 --> 14:45.570
This is the one who could surely heal his arms and legs.

14:46.511 --> 14:51.577
But the problem of getting to Jesus was almost as insurmountable as the healing itself.

14:52.818 --> 15:00.146
How could a man who can't move or walk get into the most popular house in town and get himself in front of the only one?

15:00.578 --> 15:01.319
who could heal him.

15:03.442 --> 15:04.263
Enter four men.

15:05.625 --> 15:11.212
Four men who must have been good friends of this paralytic because the task at hand was near impossible.

15:12.795 --> 15:14.497
They weren't exactly sure how they would do it.

15:14.537 --> 15:20.024
The logistics were a nightmare, but they were determined to get their friend to Jesus.

15:20.665 --> 15:24.210
So on his mat, they carried him all the way to the house.

15:26.594 --> 15:28.116
It's likely they didn't know Jesus.

15:28.256 --> 15:30.520
It's likely they didn't know the owner of the house.

15:31.261 --> 15:42.117
And I can imagine the look on their faces and the face of this paralytic man when they approached the house and saw the commotion and saw the massive amount of people.

15:43.219 --> 15:45.502
They couldn't even see the door due to the crowd.

15:48.346 --> 15:49.047
So what happened?

15:49.247 --> 15:51.190
Well, in defeat, they hung their heads.

15:51.290 --> 15:53.714
They turned for home and declared to the man,

15:53.858 --> 15:54.840
We tried our best.

15:54.880 --> 15:56.603
We gave it the old college try.

15:56.623 --> 15:58.386
It wasn't meant to be.

15:58.746 --> 15:58.927
No.

16:00.449 --> 16:00.970
Not today.

16:02.452 --> 16:08.943
These men, like the usher in the tent revival story, declared not on our watch.

16:08.963 --> 16:20.082
Driven by compassion and resolve, they carried their friend up the stairs to the roof of the house, and then in the most audaciously bold act

16:20.706 --> 16:24.752
of faith, they dug through the roof and lowered their friend to Jesus.

16:25.873 --> 16:27.876
Nothing was going to stop these four that day.

16:28.477 --> 16:30.039
Nothing was going to get in their way.

16:31.822 --> 16:45.862
Now, I know we've heard many sermons about this story, about Jesus healing the man, about the interaction with the teachers, the naysayers, and that important question, what's more difficult physical healing or spiritual healing.

16:46.743 --> 16:48.946
But today, I want to focus on these four men.

16:50.178 --> 16:58.769
and what they overcame, their unwavering resolve, and their audacious faith in the face of so many obstacles.

17:00.351 --> 17:01.532
Take a look at their obstacles.

17:04.315 --> 17:05.737
One, they didn't know Jesus.

17:06.718 --> 17:09.362
We know this because he didn't acknowledge them through the hole in the roof.

17:10.903 --> 17:16.210
Two, they weren't familiar with a homeowner, else they would have had an invitation and already been inside.

17:17.474 --> 17:20.658
Three, they couldn't get inside the door due to the swelling crowd.

17:21.379 --> 17:24.243
Four, the paralytic man on the mat was dead weight.

17:24.744 --> 17:25.044
Heavy.

17:26.126 --> 17:28.088
Have you ever tried to carry dead weight?

17:30.352 --> 17:31.473
So they were tired.

17:31.513 --> 17:35.499
Number five, they were tired from just the journey to get him to the house.

17:36.340 --> 17:39.063
Think how far they had to carry him just to get him there.

17:40.145 --> 17:42.688
Let alone the thought of carrying him up the stairs.

17:44.431 --> 17:46.834
Their arms were tired, their legs were cramping.

17:48.002 --> 17:50.787
Six, they didn't have tools to dig through the roof.

17:50.827 --> 17:52.009
They didn't come prepared.

17:52.049 --> 17:55.935
They'd likely have to use their hands.

17:57.057 --> 18:01.765
Seven, what would the people say and think about them interrupting Jesus' meeting?

18:02.666 --> 18:03.968
Eight, what would Jesus think?

18:04.890 --> 18:06.192
Would he even want to help them?

18:06.953 --> 18:09.958
Nine, what would the homeowners say about the destruction of his roof?

18:11.060 --> 18:14.706
Ten, would they be arrested, sued, end up in legal trouble?

18:15.970 --> 18:18.413
These were all very legitimate obstacles.

18:18.893 --> 18:24.999
The path to get their friend to Jesus was neither easy nor convenient nor safe.

18:26.681 --> 18:29.484
The obstacles were many, but their resolve was greater.

18:31.546 --> 18:39.855
Now, any of these obstacles could have been turned into excuses, and any of those excuses could have been used to end the mission to get their friend to Jesus.

18:41.897 --> 18:42.898
But that didn't happen.

18:44.034 --> 18:49.061
Those men didn't let obstacles turn into excuses they pressed forward.

18:50.743 --> 18:55.390
They overcame every obstacle till they got that man to the only one who could help him.

18:56.311 --> 18:57.553
And they walked away with him.

18:58.595 --> 19:01.399
He was forgiven, healed, and jumping in their midst.

19:03.742 --> 19:06.285
You know, we can make a million excuses in life.

19:06.566 --> 19:07.547
Excuses are cheap.

19:08.429 --> 19:09.490
Excuses are easy.

19:10.306 --> 19:12.028
We can justify those excuses.

19:12.088 --> 19:14.591
We can provide evidence to support them.

19:14.611 --> 19:15.913
We can build them up.

19:18.516 --> 19:23.782
You can dress up an excuse any way you want, but in the end, it's just an excuse.

19:25.764 --> 19:29.889
As was the normal routine on a Sunday morning, a wife got ready for church.

19:31.671 --> 19:37.778
She got up, she had breakfast, she put on her makeup and her clothes and was ready to go.

19:39.298 --> 19:44.484
And it was just as she was ready that she noticed her husband was still in his robe and pajamas.

19:45.886 --> 19:47.107
And she asked him, hey, what's going on?

19:48.489 --> 19:50.511
I'm not going to church, he said.

19:50.551 --> 19:53.374
What do you mean you're not going to church?

19:53.975 --> 19:56.738
Give me one good reason why you're not going to church.

19:58.340 --> 20:02.224
The husband responds, I'll give you three good reasons why I'm not going to church.

20:02.264 --> 20:04.187
Reason number one, the church feels cold.

20:05.188 --> 20:07.090
Reason number two, no one likes me.

20:08.450 --> 20:11.114
And you know what, reason number three, I just don't like it there.

20:11.134 --> 20:11.795
Is that good enough?

20:12.697 --> 20:14.159
He concluded quite proudly.

20:15.562 --> 20:19.308
Well, what if I give you three reasons why you should go to church, the wife answered?

20:20.129 --> 20:23.635
Reason number one, the church is actually quite warm and friendly.

20:24.296 --> 20:27.100
Reason number two, there's a few people there who like you.

20:28.663 --> 20:31.007
And reason number three, you're the pastor, sweetheart.

20:31.087 --> 20:33.170
So you better get dressed and go to church.

20:36.354 --> 20:38.697
We can come up with so many excuses.

20:39.758 --> 20:40.139
Endless.

20:42.021 --> 20:44.965
Have you let excuses keep you from answering God's call?

20:46.027 --> 20:48.330
Have you suppressed your conscience?

20:49.511 --> 20:52.475
Suppressed your burden because of excuses.

20:54.137 --> 20:57.361
How do we respond when we see a need to bring someone to Jesus?

20:58.423 --> 20:58.944
You've been there.

21:00.786 --> 21:03.890
A co-worker shares with you how depressed they are.

21:05.282 --> 21:09.586
A fellow student tells you how they feel empty and unfulfilled.

21:11.008 --> 21:14.612
A neighbor asks you how you handle all the stress of life.

21:16.033 --> 21:18.035
A friend questions what meaning there is in life.

21:18.416 --> 21:19.056
What's the point?

21:19.657 --> 21:20.438
What's the purpose?

21:22.199 --> 21:25.543
The opportunity is right there, right in front of you.

21:26.524 --> 21:29.347
Are you going to cower and hide your light under a bushel?

21:31.329 --> 21:32.370
Not on our watch.

21:33.794 --> 21:35.757
Like these four men, the call is clear.

21:36.519 --> 21:38.101
Bring them to Jesus.

21:39.724 --> 21:45.694
Listen, there may be legitimate obstacles in the way, but your resolve must be greater than the obstacles.

21:47.176 --> 21:50.081
So often, rather than overcoming these obstacles, we embrace them.

21:50.582 --> 21:51.944
We turn them into excuses.

21:54.528 --> 22:00.338
I want us to look today at repeated excuses that we use and have used perhaps throughout our lives.

22:01.794 --> 22:08.460
excuses that have held us back from answering God's call, from reaching those in need of Christ.

22:11.143 --> 22:14.506
One, I don't want to face ridicule.

22:16.608 --> 22:18.570
I'm embarrassed.

22:18.590 --> 22:26.597
What you're really saying here is my desire to be popular, to be liked, to be accepted exceeds my desire to stand for Christ.

22:28.139 --> 22:30.521
If I make my private beliefs public, guess what?

22:30.701 --> 22:31.442
I will be mocked.

22:32.898 --> 22:39.285
We know it's very unpopular today to be a Christian, to declare you're a Christian, to stand for what you believe.

22:41.808 --> 22:42.849
Well, I can't handle that.

22:43.310 --> 22:44.511
I can't handle that ridicule.

22:45.352 --> 22:47.014
Friend, it's a problem of priorities.

22:47.875 --> 22:50.357
Do we prioritize popularity over conviction?

22:51.979 --> 22:53.561
Acceptance over conviction?

22:54.882 --> 22:56.484
What does Scripture have to say about this?

22:57.385 --> 22:58.787
Look at 1 Peter 4, 14.

23:00.669 --> 23:01.810
If you're insulted

23:02.082 --> 23:07.830
because of the name of Christ you are blessed, for the spirit of glory and of God rests on you.

23:08.932 --> 23:18.525
Matthew 5, 11, and 12, blessed are you when people insult you, persecute you, and falsely say all kinds of evil against you because of me.

23:19.146 --> 23:26.797
Rejoice and be glad because great is your reward in heaven, for in the same way they persecuted the prophets who were before you.

23:28.219 --> 23:30.322
Listen, persecution and ridicule

23:31.874 --> 23:34.677
come to all believers who live their faith openly.

23:35.718 --> 23:39.022
But the Holy Spirit gives comfort and strength to remain faithful.

23:39.883 --> 23:48.031
We can stand tall during these times knowing that though God will bring judgment to everyone, He will be faithful to uphold us.

23:49.133 --> 23:53.357
And He uses these tests to build us, to grow us and strengthen us.

23:56.601 --> 23:57.442
Look at His example.

23:58.443 --> 24:01.586
Stay focused on the mission and ignore the ridicule.

24:01.794 --> 24:05.861
few chapters later, Rick shared this earlier in the month.

24:06.462 --> 24:10.428
There's a story about a man named Jairus who came to see Jesus.

24:14.214 --> 24:15.436
And he came and he begged him.

24:15.636 --> 24:19.823
He begged him earnestly and he said, Jesus, my little daughter is dying.

24:20.184 --> 24:20.644
She's sick.

24:21.205 --> 24:22.147
Please come and heal her.

24:22.868 --> 24:28.337
And while he was still speaking to Jesus, someone from his household came and said, it's too late.

24:28.697 --> 24:29.138
She died.

24:30.338 --> 24:32.261
Don't trouble the teacher anymore.

24:33.943 --> 24:36.387
When Jesus heard this, he said to Jairus, don't be afraid.

24:36.908 --> 24:37.649
Only believe.

24:38.571 --> 24:40.233
And he took three of his disciples.

24:40.253 --> 24:41.655
They went to Jairus' house.

24:42.917 --> 24:45.281
When they got there, they saw a large crowd weeping.

24:45.321 --> 24:48.506
When he came in, he told them, why?

24:48.566 --> 24:49.627
Why all this commotion?

24:50.409 --> 24:51.530
The child is not dead.

24:51.650 --> 24:52.612
She's just sleeping.

24:53.834 --> 24:56.658
And they ridiculed him.

24:58.466 --> 25:03.613
They'd seen him perform miracle after miracle, but still they doubted.

25:03.633 --> 25:06.116
They mocked and they ridiculed him.

25:08.459 --> 25:09.701
So he put them all outside.

25:10.582 --> 25:15.689
He took the father and the mother of the child along with those who are with him and they, they entered where the child was.

25:17.732 --> 25:25.682
He took her by the hand and said, little girl, I say to you, arise and immediately the girl arose and walked.

25:26.402 --> 25:29.706
And those present in the room were overcome with great amazement.

25:31.288 --> 25:33.571
Did he stop to address the ridicule?

25:35.473 --> 25:36.134
No.

25:36.154 --> 25:37.897
Did he fire back at the scoffers?

25:38.537 --> 25:39.398
That's what I would have done.

25:40.480 --> 25:40.740
Nice.

25:40.840 --> 25:41.401
Good zinger.

25:41.461 --> 25:42.743
He's God.

25:42.803 --> 25:43.544
He could have done it.

25:44.365 --> 25:44.785
He didn't.

25:46.487 --> 25:49.571
He stayed true to his mission, and he ignored the ridicule.

25:50.733 --> 25:54.898
He let his actions speak as his defense.

25:55.714 --> 25:57.076
ignore the ridicule friend.

25:57.116 --> 26:03.687
Our mission for Christ is more important than our acceptance by the world or our popularity within it.

26:06.612 --> 26:09.496
So one, I don't want to face ridicule.

26:09.557 --> 26:11.019
Two, I don't want to face rejection.

26:11.820 --> 26:16.107
Not only will I be mocked, not only will I be shunned, I'll be canceled.

26:18.211 --> 26:20.514
I'll lose my standing within my circle.

26:21.536 --> 26:22.738
My ego can't take it.

26:24.898 --> 26:25.920
Look to the Savior again.

26:26.741 --> 26:31.448
Isaiah 53.3 tells us he was despised and rejected by men.

26:32.690 --> 26:37.777
John 1.11 says he came to his own, but his own did not receive him.

26:41.062 --> 26:45.809
Look at all the rejection Jesus faced at every turn, at every point in his life.

26:46.330 --> 26:48.393
He faced rejection from family members.

26:49.415 --> 26:51.698
Scripture tells us not even his brothers believed in him.

26:52.962 --> 26:55.625
Jesus, his own family, rejected him as the Messiah.

26:56.507 --> 26:58.249
In his life among us, he was a son.

26:58.309 --> 27:00.752
He was a brother, maybe even an uncle.

27:04.657 --> 27:10.845
But those relationships broke his heart because he was rejected by every one of them.

27:12.867 --> 27:18.514
His love wasn't returned, wasn't wanted, wasn't accepted, rejected by his family.

27:18.775 --> 27:21.298
He was rejected by his community.

27:22.466 --> 27:30.374
When Jesus returned to his hometown of Nazareth, we said that his ministry base was Capernaum, not his hometown of Nazareth.

27:30.414 --> 27:30.694
Why?

27:31.154 --> 27:44.487
Well, when he returned there, his hometown, where he grew up, his neighbors, his friends, his family, he said he was without honor in his hometown.

27:44.547 --> 27:46.069
They took offense at him.

27:47.070 --> 27:51.634
Scripture even tells us that he didn't do many mighty works there because of their unbelief.

27:53.026 --> 28:00.793
He knows what it's like to lose the love and support of a community, to feel unwelcome in a place that was once home.

28:01.975 --> 28:14.246
And in the ultimate rejection, his own people, when he was presented to them by Pilate, they chose murderous Barabbas instead.

28:15.627 --> 28:22.514
And they declared their hatred for Jesus.

28:23.842 --> 28:25.665
by demanding his crucifixion.

28:27.448 --> 28:28.831
That's rejection.

28:28.851 --> 28:31.395
He was rejected by family members, by community.

28:32.337 --> 28:36.103
He faced rejection from people who once claimed to love him.

28:37.826 --> 28:43.256
In O Christ and his divinity, he predicted both Judas' betrayal and Peter's denial.

28:44.137 --> 28:49.266
He saw both of them coming, but in his humanness, he still experienced the hurt.

28:51.618 --> 28:55.283
Jesus was troubled in his spirit as he foretold of Judas.

28:56.784 --> 28:58.887
Think about it, he had just washed the guy's feet.

28:59.868 --> 29:03.192
Few verses earlier symbolizing the laying down of his very life for him.

29:04.534 --> 29:16.789
And Peter, oh Peter, Peter who professed his love and commitment to Jesus more ardently than any other would reject even an association with Jesus in a matter of hours.

29:18.071 --> 29:20.594
Sudden, total, heartbreaking rejection.

29:21.218 --> 29:22.019
Jesus felt it.

29:23.300 --> 29:25.063
He faced rejection from his father.

29:26.484 --> 29:31.230
The night of his arrest, we read that Jesus was very sorrowful even to death.

29:31.630 --> 29:36.736
We're told in the Garden of Gethsemane as he prayed, he would sweat, drops of blood.

29:37.697 --> 29:40.421
He was overcome with anguish and grief.

29:42.243 --> 29:48.370
And I think it was more than the thoughts of the approaching physical pain that put Jesus in that state.

29:49.570 --> 29:54.916
I think it was the knowledge that he would soon be separated from and abandoned by his father.

29:57.639 --> 30:03.946
As he hung on the cross, dying, he cried out, my God, my God, why have you forsaken me?

30:04.868 --> 30:08.171
Notice he didn't cry, why am I in such pain?

30:08.932 --> 30:10.434
Why do I have to go through this?

30:10.954 --> 30:11.155
No.

30:12.336 --> 30:13.938
Father, why have you forsaken me?

30:15.420 --> 30:17.522
He faced rejection at every turn.

30:18.242 --> 30:20.846
And lastly, from you and from me, for years.

30:21.868 --> 30:26.916
How many years did he suffer rejection from us until we finally opened our hearts to him?

30:28.698 --> 30:36.791
If he can go through all of that for us, can we not go through a sliver of potential rejection for him?

30:38.774 --> 30:43.722
Three, I'm not equipped the Moses argument.

30:44.443 --> 30:46.226
We talked about this Wednesday, man.

30:47.394 --> 30:52.401
Remember the famous quote, God doesn't call the equipped, He equips the called.

30:52.781 --> 30:53.362
I love that.

30:54.263 --> 30:59.210
But before we go on, we have to make sure the call is there, that that's in place first.

31:00.632 --> 31:04.417
It's very important that we are following God's will and not our own desire.

31:05.719 --> 31:13.709
We may want to change everyone's world, but God has called us specifically to the harvest field He has ordained for us.

31:13.729 --> 31:14.290
Amen?

31:15.042 --> 31:17.946
If you're trying to harvest the field of your own choosing, it won't go well.

31:18.407 --> 31:21.331
No matter how hard you try, no matter how much you may want it.

31:23.274 --> 31:30.205
It may never be for you or it may be for you one day, but not today, not now.

31:30.605 --> 31:34.792
God has called you to a specific field in a specific time.

31:36.895 --> 31:38.938
Follow his will in his timing.

31:40.260 --> 31:41.682
And now if you know it's his will,

31:43.010 --> 31:44.251
You know he's calling you.

31:44.291 --> 31:45.353
You feel the burden.

31:45.793 --> 31:46.634
You know it's him.

31:46.674 --> 31:50.939
And you still feel unprepared or inadequate, get in line.

31:52.961 --> 31:53.562
You're not alone.

31:53.942 --> 31:58.928
Throughout scripture, God has called ordinary people to extraordinary missions.

32:00.089 --> 32:02.752
He doesn't expect you to have all the answers from the start.

32:04.254 --> 32:08.338
He promises to equip you with everything you need as you need it.

32:09.986 --> 32:13.051
as long as you're willing to trust Him and step out in faith.

32:14.373 --> 32:16.275
Always ask yourself, has He called me to this?

32:17.417 --> 32:18.459
If so, He'll equip you.

32:19.260 --> 32:20.201
Step out in faith.

32:20.582 --> 32:24.307
And listen, no one is asking you to stand on the debate floor.

32:25.769 --> 32:27.672
No, just speak of your life.

32:27.853 --> 32:29.495
Are you equipped to speak of yourself?

32:30.476 --> 32:31.438
Then tell your story.

32:33.020 --> 32:34.342
Share about your experience.

32:34.362 --> 32:35.604
What has Christ done for you?

32:36.365 --> 32:37.988
Why did you open your heart to Him?

32:38.048 --> 32:39.570
How has He changed your life?

32:41.538 --> 32:44.983
That's more influential than any debate argument you can make.

32:45.944 --> 32:50.751
A heartfelt experience will draw people in more than you can imagine.

32:53.194 --> 32:55.958
Excuse number four, I'm not the right person.

32:56.038 --> 32:56.619
I'm flawed.

32:58.081 --> 32:58.962
I won't be effective.

33:00.724 --> 33:02.567
Friend Moses stuttered.

33:03.829 --> 33:04.850
Miriam was a gossip.

33:06.052 --> 33:07.794
Jonah ran from God.

33:08.514 --> 33:09.776
Leo was unattractive.

33:09.876 --> 33:12.600
Paul saw himself as the chief of sinners.

33:13.322 --> 33:14.443
Peter was impulsive.

33:14.483 --> 33:15.285
He had a temper.

33:15.926 --> 33:16.987
Martha was a warrior.

33:17.108 --> 33:18.410
Samson was codependent.

33:18.750 --> 33:20.072
Joseph was abused.

33:21.134 --> 33:22.737
Mark was rejected by Paul.

33:22.837 --> 33:23.858
Zacchaeus was short.

33:24.179 --> 33:25.281
Naomi was a widow.

33:25.721 --> 33:26.963
Thomas had his doubts.

33:27.063 --> 33:28.185
Jacob was a cheater.

33:28.626 --> 33:29.768
Elijah was moody.

33:29.948 --> 33:31.090
Sarah was impatient.

33:31.651 --> 33:33.153
Abraham was deceitful.

33:34.155 --> 33:36.338
And God used every one of them.

33:37.410 --> 33:46.100
in such historic ways that their stories are etched into the pages of Scripture and into our hearts forever and ever.

33:46.401 --> 33:47.442
Can he not use you?

33:49.464 --> 33:51.807
Besides, it's not what you bring to the table.

33:51.867 --> 33:53.589
It's what he brings through you.

33:54.450 --> 33:55.191
Be his vessel.

33:55.391 --> 33:56.232
Let him work in you.

33:57.594 --> 33:59.736
Five, it's not the right timing.

34:01.598 --> 34:02.179
Who's timing?

34:03.420 --> 34:04.722
God's timing or yours?

34:05.442 --> 34:09.627
If the opportunity has presented itself, it was engineered by God.

34:11.209 --> 34:15.093
This excuses as thin as the, I don't have peace about this, I've preached on that.

34:16.435 --> 34:27.527
God has brought the opportunity to your door to stand for Him, to share about Him, to witness for Him, to help someone in His name, to reach a life for Him, seize it.

34:29.109 --> 34:33.554
It doesn't need analysis, it doesn't need peace, it doesn't need comfort or convenience.

34:33.794 --> 34:35.596
You don't need to check your schedule.

34:36.618 --> 34:38.160
Seize the opportunity.

34:38.921 --> 34:44.869
Second Corinthians 6-2 says, I tell you, now is the time of God's favor.

34:45.450 --> 34:47.473
Now is the day of salvation.

34:48.494 --> 34:52.279
Step up for Christ right now when the opportunity is passing by.

34:55.443 --> 34:57.787
And lastly, six, I won't be successful.

34:58.848 --> 35:00.370
Here's where our perspective is off.

35:01.474 --> 35:02.595
Let me be clear about this.

35:02.655 --> 35:12.685
The success of our ministry, of our service to God is not by our hands, through our efforts, by our talent, articulation, influence, or persuasiveness.

35:13.306 --> 35:15.088
We do what God asks of us.

35:16.349 --> 35:17.830
We serve as He leads us.

35:18.091 --> 35:23.696
We go through the doors He opens, and the success of our efforts are brought from God.

35:26.038 --> 35:26.859
We sow the seed.

35:27.760 --> 35:28.581
We plant it.

35:29.162 --> 35:29.682
That's it.

35:30.786 --> 35:31.186
That's it.

35:31.226 --> 35:32.448
Can we make it take root?

35:33.489 --> 35:33.709
No.

35:33.789 --> 35:34.830
Can we make it grow?

35:35.450 --> 35:35.631
No.

35:35.691 --> 35:36.872
Can we bring the rain?

35:36.932 --> 35:37.212
No.

35:38.333 --> 35:39.114
That's up to God.

35:39.895 --> 35:42.437
Do your part and leave the rest to Him.

35:44.439 --> 35:46.701
Don't think you can make your efforts successful.

35:46.721 --> 35:50.224
You'll disappoint yourself every single time.

35:50.685 --> 35:51.646
Only God can do that.

35:52.446 --> 35:55.850
Give Him your best and leave the success of it to Him.

35:56.810 --> 35:57.111
Amen?

35:59.813 --> 36:00.594
Our time is up.

36:02.050 --> 36:03.892
The bottom line, dear friend, is this.

36:05.434 --> 36:10.921
There's no good excuse that should stand in the way when God is asking something of you.

36:12.262 --> 36:22.695
If he has brought the opportunity to your door, if he has brought the person to your door who is searching, who is seeking, don't let anything stand in the way of you answering that call.

36:25.158 --> 36:31.826
You know, God has put people in your life so that you can reach them for Christ, so that you can

36:32.002 --> 36:33.124
Bring them to Jesus.

36:34.726 --> 36:36.128
What is God asking of you today?

36:38.632 --> 36:47.464
Is God calling you to reach someone for Him, to tell someone about Him, to help someone in some way for which you are uniquely positioned?

36:49.447 --> 36:50.929
It may be a stranger on the street.

36:51.971 --> 36:54.354
It may be a friend or a neighbor or a coworker.

36:55.356 --> 36:59.762
Your calling right now may be to your children, to the people in your household.

37:01.154 --> 37:05.380
Whatever they ask, don't let obstacles become excuses.

37:06.741 --> 37:08.964
Don't let distractions become excuses.

37:10.366 --> 37:12.689
Don't let insecurities become excuses.

37:12.729 --> 37:14.652
Don't let fears become excuses.

37:15.793 --> 37:19.538
You've been prepared for such a time as this.

37:19.819 --> 37:21.040
Remember Esther's story?

37:23.163 --> 37:28.530
You have come to your position and you are uniquely qualified for such a time as this.

37:30.338 --> 37:37.349
God has orchestrated the circumstance and he's placed you in the perfect position to change somebody's world.

37:39.172 --> 37:39.993
How will you respond?

37:41.295 --> 37:46.543
Like those four men who carried their paralytic friend on his mat, will you bring them to Jesus?

37:48.466 --> 37:53.373
Will you seize the moment, overcome the obstacles and fears and serve the Savior?

37:54.776 --> 37:58.962
Or will you let the opportunity pass by because of excuses?

38:00.962 --> 38:01.964
Not on my watch.

38:03.466 --> 38:04.888
Don't let that moment slip away.

38:05.910 --> 38:07.592
Don't let that person slip away.

38:08.814 --> 38:11.298
Don't let that call slip away.

38:12.500 --> 38:13.221
Be determined.

38:14.342 --> 38:19.050
Step out in faith for Christ and change somebody's world today.

38:19.951 --> 38:20.272
Amen.

38:20.973 --> 38:21.413
Let's pray.

38:23.356 --> 38:29.746
Heavenly Father, you have called each one of us to reach those in our circle.

38:31.202 --> 38:35.308
Our friends, our relatives, our coworkers, our neighbors, our children.

38:36.791 --> 38:44.202
Help us, Lord, to overcome the excuses and the obstacles and give of ourselves fully.

38:46.345 --> 38:53.556
Help us to stand for you, to speak of you, to live for you and to live our lives sold out for your kingdom.

38:55.199 --> 38:59.986
And one day in heaven, we will see those who benefited from our efforts.

39:00.450 --> 39:11.147
who saw Christ in us and came to Him, and we will hear your voice telling us, well done, good and faithful servant.

39:11.167 --> 39:11.607
Thank you.

39:14.031 --> 39:18.198
Thank you, Father, for the opportunities with which you entrust us.

39:18.739 --> 39:22.985
May we seize them and serve you with all we are and with all we have.

39:23.927 --> 39:27.292
In the precious name of your Son, Jesus Christ, we pray.

39:28.314 --> 39:28.594
Amen.

